review_blob: I first experienced this beer in 1961, when it sold for .69 a six-pack. For reference Shlitz and Budweiser sold for $1.29, Busch (then called "Busch Bavarian") and Old Milwaukee were $1.09. I have no idea why this beer was (and still apparently is) brewed in Auburndale, FL - but the worst beer in America being brewed in area once exclusively associated with processing phosphorous makes some sort of sense.
